CMP.verdict+='<div class="card"><h2>👨‍👩‍👧‍👦 Family Pros & Cons</h2><div class="table-wrap"><table><tr><th></th><th style="color:var(--accent)">Melbourne ✅ Pros</th><th style="color:var(--accent)">Melbourne ❌ Cons</th></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Money</td><td>$15k/yr cheaper. More savings. Better surplus.</td><td>Higher heating bills in winter</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Schools</td><td>Better zoned govt schools (91+ scores). Glen Waverley SC excellent.</td><td>Fewer selective schools, entry from Year 9 not 7</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Bella (circus)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">NICA — national circus centre. Best in AU for aerial.</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Jack (ice/circus)</td><td>Oakleigh rink 15 min from Glen Waverley. NICA for circus too.</td><td>Fewer rinks than Sydney</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Frankie (work)</td><td style="color:var(--green)">Higher pay ($55–75k). Strong demand in VIC schools.</td><td>—</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Lifestyle</td><td>Coffee, food, culture, AFL, F1, Australian Open</td><td>Colder winters. Less sunshine. No iconic beaches.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Family settling</td><td>Compact eastern suburbs. Everything close together.</td><td>"Four seasons in one day" weather</td></tr></table></div><div class="table-wrap"><table><tr><th></th><th style="color:var(--orange)">Sydney ✅ Pros</th><th style="color:var(--orange)">Sydney ❌ Cons</th></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Money</td><td>—</td><td style="color:var(--red)">$15k/yr more expensive. Tighter budget.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Schools</td><td>Larger selective school network from Year 7</td><td>Weaker zoned govt schools (89 vs 91)</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Bella (circus)</td><td>Sydney Trapeze School is good</td><td>No equivalent to NICA. Fewer aerial options.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Jack (ice/circus)</td><td>More ice rinks across Sydney</td><td>Rinks more spread out, longer travel</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Frankie (work)</td><td>Good job market</td><td>Slightly lower pay ($50–72k). More competitive.</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Lifestyle</td><td style="color:var(--green)">World-class beaches. Warmer. More sunshine.</td><td>Longer commutes from family suburbs</td></tr><tr><td style="font-weight:600">Family settling</td><td>Harbour lifestyle, outdoor living</td><td>More spread out. Harder to find affordable + good school + safe</td></tr></table></div></div>';

CMP.verdict+='<div class="card" style="border-left:4px solid var(--green)"><h2>🎯 For the Prater-Cockaynes Specifically</h2><p class="ts" style="line-height:2">Based on your family\'s specific needs:</p><ul class="ts" style="margin:8px 0 0 20px;line-height:2.2"><li><strong>Bella\'s aerial/circus</strong> → Melbourne (NICA is unbeatable)</li><li><strong>Jack\'s ice skating + circus</strong> → Slight Melbourne edge (Oakleigh rink + NICA)</li><li><strong>Frankie\'s career</strong> → Melbourne (better pay, more demand)</li><li><strong>School quality</strong> → Melbourne (Glen Waverley SC 91.40)</li><li><strong>Budget</strong> → Melbourne ($15k/yr more surplus)</li><li><strong>Weather/beaches</strong> → Sydney (only area Sydney clearly wins)</li></ul><p class="ts mt2" style="font-weight:700;font-size:1.1rem;color:var(--accent)">Score: Melbourne 5 — Sydney 1</p><p class="ts mt2">The numbers and your family\'s specific interests both point to Melbourne. Sydney\'s advantage is lifestyle (beaches, weather) — which is real but costs $15k/yr for the privilege.</p></div>';

